5:
Chairman, perhaps you should take
a break? I brought you tea.
9:
Ah, Mizuchi. Thank you for going to
the trouble.
12:
...Lately, the old artist is doing
whatever he likes on a whim. He's
more trouble than the fox, I daresay.
16:
Are you referring to his request to
browse books banned by the
Diviners' Commission?
20:
Yes, but not only that. He wishes to
include Kugui's art in that
encyclopedia of his!
23:
If her art were to be featured... That
would no doubt invite calamity
greater even than the first volume!
26:
Surely Miss Kugui will not allow that
to happen...
29:
...I suppose you're right. Surely the
sequel won't be as bad as the
original.
34:
Well, I for one am glad that she can
now paint again.
38:
Indeed. It was an unexpected, but
not unwelcome, surprise for her to
overcome her fears in that situation.
40:
Though I cannot pretend to
understand how that Ryouki
managed to help her through it.
43:
It may have been a struggle that
only a fellow artist could have
insight into.
46:
...Speaking of artist struggles, she's
always had a habit of being so
absorbed in her work that she
forgets to eat and sleep.
48:
Artists are beyond the scope of our
comprehension, I suppose.
51:
She's staying in that old artist's
home now, isn't she? I do hope she's
all right.
52:
I half expect the lot of them to be
collapsed from exhaustion and
malnourishment. Perhaps I should
send a shikigami to check in—
57:
Chairman, you're being a little
overprotective...
63: Gramp Zigza! It is I, Inaho!
65:
How is the encyclopedia coming
along? More importantly, have you
made any progress on KoiAzu?
72:
Fox kits... I count one, two...
A lot of them.
76:
What's going on? Awa, Hie, Mugi!
When did you learn how to multiply?!
83: Ah, it's you folks. Whaddya want?
87:
Errr, mind explaining what's going on
with the foxes first?
94:
I asked for a whole heap, since
they're useful little fellas for house
work.
96:
Folks are starting to call us the Yokai
Mansion because of it. But the kids
love it, so there's no issue.
101:
Hey! They do not exist for your
convenience, you know!
106: They look so soft... and fluffy...
111: In any case, is Kugui here?
116:
Sorry to say, but she's out. The real
fox kits are showing her to some
yokai. Y'know, for painting.
119:
They didn't go far, so they should be
back by lunch. We can wait for them
inside.
141:
Are you okay? You don't need to
push yourself...
143:
Sorry I'm slowing you down... But this
mountain path stretches on forever!
I can't help being beat...
149:
Well... Compared to fighting yokai,
hiking up a mountain is fairly tame.
153:
Yeah, I figured... Maybe I should start
working out too. Can't hurt to buff
up, right?
161:
A silly part of me would be sad that I
wouldn't need to be your protector
anymore.
165:
Don't worry, Kugui! I'll never be a
match for big bad monsters no
matter how much I train!
169:
...Perhaps a bit of physical training
might be helpful?
171:
Enough to be able to run, just in
case. Thinking about it now...
there's a chance the nue I paint
today could grow violent.
175:
I don't care what happens. I'm not
leaving you behind, even if you tell
me to run.
178:
...Then I'll make sure we never get to
that point.
181:
Maybe you should do the painting
instead. I need to conserve energy
so I can defend us.
184: What? But I wanna watch you paint!
191:
Back when you were about to fight
the dragon... What were you going
to say before I cut you off?
196:
...Don't worry about that. It was only
going to be embarrassing
nonsense, since I let the blood rush
to my head...
200:
Well, now I wanna know even more!
Tell me!
203:
I refuse! Besides... It was something
that already came true.
